    &lt;CommentText&gt;Thank you for taking the time to write in about your recent experience when attending a clinic appointment at the Rheumatology Department at Russells Hall Hospital. 
We are sorry to hear about the issues you encountered as a result of the last minute cancellation of the clinic owing you due to unforeseen circumstances. Please be assured that we make every effort to provide the highest standards and we are disappointed this was not the case on this occasion. We really appreciate how frustrating it is and have shared your feedback with the senior team responsible with a request that consideration is given to preventing a repeat of this issue in the future.  
Should you not receive a new date and time for your clinic appointment in the near future, we strongly urge you to contact our Patient Advice Liaison Service (PALS) who will be able to assist you further.  They can be contacted by telephone 0800 073 0510 or by email dgft.pals@nhs.net&lt;/CommentText&gt;
